Published in 1946, Dispersal Sale of the Cloverdale Herd of Scotch Shorthorns is a catalog detailing the sale of a prestigious herd of Shorthorn cattle, some bred originally in Crediton, Ontario. This document provides a snapshot of mid-20th-century livestock breeding in Canada, listing pedigrees, lineage details, and sale logistics for breeders, farmers, and agricultural historians interested in livestock heritage.
